verbose_text: The relevance of hyperandrogenism is documented by genetic, clinical and experimental studies that have documented the pivotal pathogenic role of androgen excess in the generation and perpetuation of the syndrome, as epitomized by the contribution of genetic variants of DENN domain containing 1 (DENND1A), which is expressed in androgen producing theca cells of the ovary and whose overexpression causes hyperandrogenism and a PCOS phenotype.
